cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper is about using Item Response Theory (IRT) to generate a gold-standard test set for evaluating NLP systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the comparison of NLP system performance with human performance, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of IRT in psychometrics, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
